01:11:26.415 --> 01:11:28.661
<i>including extortion
and money laundering.</i>

1373
01:11:28.685 --> 01:11:30.996
[woman] Today is the day
that many in this city

1374
01:11:31.020 --> 01:11:33.354
thought would never come.

1375
01:11:33.422 --> 01:11:36.891
James J. "Whitey" Bulger
now stands convicted

1376
01:11:36.958 --> 01:11:39.405
for his role as the ring leader

1377
01:11:39.429 --> 01:11:41.940
of the murderous
Winter Hill Gang.

1378
01:11:41.964 --> 01:11:44.299
<i>This day of reckoning for Bulger</i>

1379
01:11:44.366 --> 01:11:46.567
<i>has been a long time in coming.</i>

1380
01:11:49.304 --> 01:11:54.019
<i>Jim Bulger is my uncle.
and he's still family to me.</i>

1381
01:11:54.043 --> 01:12:00.081
But I am aware that now.
in retrospect. he hurt people

1382
01:12:02.918 --> 01:12:06.165
<i>The families that were left.
some kids that I played with</i>

1383
01:12:06.189 --> 01:12:08.233
<i>when I was younger.
who didn't have a father</i>

1384
01:12:08.257 --> 01:12:11.103
<i>and I didn't realize
until 30 or 40 years later</i>

1385
01:12:11.127 --> 01:12:13.995
<i>why they didn't have a father.</i>

1386
01:12:14.062 --> 01:12:17.532
[man]<i> There's no way to equate
what our family has gone through</i>

1387
01:12:17.599 --> 01:12:21.813
<i>with what the victims of the
crime families have gone through.</i>

1388
01:12:21.837 --> 01:12:23.471
<i>They've suffered terribly.</i>

1389
01:12:23.538 --> 01:12:26.174
The Bulgers are not
in that bucket.

1390
01:12:29.211 --> 01:12:30.878
[Catherine]
<i>It's very difficult for me.</i>

1391
01:12:30.946 --> 01:12:34.148
<i>almost impossible for me to say</i>

1392
01:12:34.216 --> 01:12:35.883
<i>he was like this.</i>

1393
01:12:35.951 --> 01:12:38.286
<i>and this is the way I was
with him in Santa Monica</i>

1394
01:12:38.353 --> 01:12:39.665
<i>and how he lived</i>

1395
01:12:39.689 --> 01:12:41.333
and he did that.

1396
01:12:41.357 --> 01:12:44.603
I mean.
it's hard for me to see that

1397
01:12:44.627 --> 01:12:47.940
but I'm not diminishing
their suffering at all.

1398
01:12:47.964 --> 01:12:49.864
I mean. I know they lost people.

1399
01:12:51.166 --> 01:12:52.900
Uh...

1400
01:12:54.102 --> 01:12:56.671
I don't know. I'm sorry.

1401
01:12:58.707 --> 01:13:01.175
[brooding piano tune]

1402
01:13:13.588 --> 01:13:17.458
[Jean Bulger Holland]
<i>I feel sorry for him at times.</i>

1403
01:13:17.526 --> 01:13:19.705
<i>Then I could be angry.</i>

1404
01:13:19.729 --> 01:13:22.574
<i>He's been his own worst enemy.</i>

1405
01:13:22.598 --> 01:13:26.000
<i>And I know
he never expected the fallout.</i>

1406
01:13:26.067 --> 01:13:28.803
But you don't even know--
Does he have the capacity.

1407
01:13:28.870 --> 01:13:32.607
for him to look beyond
what his own little life is.

1408
01:13:32.674 --> 01:13:33.719
you know.

1409
01:13:33.743 --> 01:13:37.211
and see how it's
affected anybody else?

1410
01:13:37.279 --> 01:13:39.914
I'm not sure that he...
He goes there.

1411
01:13:42.151 --> 01:13:43.351
[William] <i>I wrote to him</i>

1412
01:13:43.418 --> 01:13:46.187
<i>all the years he was in prison.</i>

1413
01:13:47.222 --> 01:13:49.524
You know. I cared...
I care about him.

1414
01:13:50.692 --> 01:13:52.693
I'm not sure

1415
01:13:52.761 --> 01:13:54.896
if he was listening
attentively to me.

1416
01:14:02.237 --> 01:14:04.016
[woman] <i>I really loved my mother</i>

1417
01:14:04.040 --> 01:14:06.774
<i>but could never express it
with words.</i>

1418
01:14:08.243 --> 01:14:10.355
<i>Fortunately.
my brother Bill could</i>

1419
01:14:10.379 --> 01:14:13.181
<i>and always said the right
things to her and my father</i>

1420
01:14:13.248 --> 01:14:14.916
<i>in their last moments.</i>

1421
01:14:14.983 --> 01:14:16.762
"I can see the room."

1422
01:14:16.786 --> 01:14:20.188
"My mother in it in so much pain"

1423
01:14:20.255 --> 01:14:22.490
"but I couldn't do
anything for her."

1424
01:14:25.327 --> 01:14:27.639
<i>After the trial.
I wanted to find out</i>

1425
01:14:27.663 --> 01:14:31.910
<i>what we were told. and I went
to the Plymouth Prison</i>

1426
01:14:31.934 --> 01:14:33.512
and got Bulger's information.

1427
01:14:33.536 --> 01:14:35.336
He was an inmate there.

1428
01:14:35.403 --> 01:14:37.271
And find out
how to write to him.

1429
01:14:37.339 --> 01:14:38.584
And I did send him a letter

1430
01:14:38.608 --> 01:14:40.341
and explained
that I was on the jury

1431
01:14:40.408 --> 01:14:41.876
and I just had questions.

1432
01:14:43.478 --> 01:14:46.347
<i>When he talked
about the criminality</i>

1433
01:14:46.414 --> 01:14:48.616
<i>there was a harshness to him.</i>

1434
01:14:48.683 --> 01:14:51.619
<i>But then he would start
talking about his family.</i>

1435
01:14:51.686 --> 01:14:54.466
and there would be
just this softness

1436
01:14:54.490 --> 01:14:56.591
a kindness. a compassion.

1437
01:14:58.894 --> 01:15:02.964
Even in the very first letters.
Jim talked about Catherine

1438
01:15:03.031 --> 01:15:06.234
and how he had wanted
to take the death sentence

1439
01:15:06.301 --> 01:15:08.436
and have her get out of prison.

1440
01:15:10.772 --> 01:15:13.085
[newsreader]<i> "Whitey" Bulger's</i>
<i>girlfriend. Catherine Greig.</i>

1441
01:15:13.109 --> 01:15:14.953
<i>just learned that she'll spend</i>

1442
01:15:14.977 --> 01:15:17.111
<i>an additional 21 months
behind bars.</i>

1443
01:15:17.178 --> 01:15:18.579
<i>almost two years.</i>

1444
01:15:18.647 --> 01:15:20.314
Greig is already serving
an eight year sentence

1445
01:15:20.382 --> 01:15:21.883
for helping Bulger
evade capture.

1446
01:15:24.119 --> 01:15:26.187
[man]<i> The government wanted</i>
<i>to punish her</i>

1447
01:15:26.254 --> 01:15:28.523
<i>because it was the only way
they could really get</i>

1448
01:15:28.590 --> 01:15:30.992
<i>at Jim Bulger.
make him hurt more.</i>

1449
01:15:31.059 --> 01:15:35.463
The judge allowed every
alleged victim of Jim Bulger

1450
01:15:35.530 --> 01:15:38.933
who had no relevance
whatsoever to Catherine Greig

1451
01:15:39.000 --> 01:15:40.134
to come into court

1452
01:15:40.201 --> 01:15:42.114
and call her
a dirty little bitch.

1453
01:15:42.138 --> 01:15:45.517
And they yelled at her.
and the...

1454
01:15:45.541 --> 01:15:48.142
No judge should allow
their courtroom

1455
01:15:48.209 --> 01:15:49.677
to be used like that.

1456
01:15:49.744 --> 01:15:50.978
It was disgusting.

1457
01:15:52.681 --> 01:15:56.795
[Catherine] <i>I didn't have a
trial. I pled guilty to the charges.</i>

1458
01:15:56.819 --> 01:16:00.154
but my sentence was still
the longest in US history

1459
01:16:00.221 --> 01:16:01.556
for what I was charged with.

1460
01:16:04.092 --> 01:16:07.828
<i>I wasn't given that long
sentence for what I did.</i>

1461
01:16:07.896 --> 01:16:09.408
<i>I was given that long sentence</i>

1462
01:16:09.432 --> 01:16:11.232
<i>and the last thing
the judge said to me</i>

1463
01:16:11.299 --> 01:16:12.811
<i>when I left the courtroom was.</i>

1464
01:16:12.835 --> 01:16:15.303
"Now. if you come back
and speak to us."

1465
01:16:15.370 --> 01:16:16.504
'cause I wouldn't
talk to them...

1466
01:16:16.571 --> 01:16:17.905
"If you come back
and speak to us"

1467
01:16:17.973 --> 01:16:20.085
"we'll be glad to revisit this."

1468
01:16:20.109 --> 01:16:22.421
And I thought.
"How outrageous is this?"

1469
01:16:22.445 --> 01:16:27.048
And I didn't understand then
that what they did to people

1470
01:16:27.115 --> 01:16:31.229
was give them a pass if they
told. not even the truth.

1471
01:16:31.253 --> 01:16:34.032
but they told
their version of the truth.

1472
01:16:34.056 --> 01:16:35.389
And that. unfortunately

1473
01:16:35.457 --> 01:16:37.502
is what has become
of our justice system

1474
01:16:37.526 --> 01:16:39.026
which I think is horrendous.

1475
01:16:43.732 --> 01:16:45.533
[gentle music]

1476
01:17:06.355 --> 01:17:07.888
[Jason Bowns]
<i>I think Bill Bulger</i>

1477
01:17:07.956 --> 01:17:09.624
<i>wanted to be judged
for what he did</i>

1478
01:17:12.828 --> 01:17:14.762
<i>and not
for what his brother did.</i>

1479
01:17:14.829 --> 01:17:16.897
<i>And I think people.
for some reason.</i>

1480
01:17:16.965 --> 01:17:19.767
<i>they're just fascinated
by the crime stuff.</i>

1481
01:17:21.503 --> 01:17:22.970
<i>You know.
it really hit home to me</i>

1482
01:17:23.038 --> 01:17:25.373
<i>when I was calling UMass Boston.</i>

1483
01:17:25.440 --> 01:17:26.952
<i>I was asking them
to help me track down</i>

1484
01:17:26.976 --> 01:17:28.342
<i>an article in the library.</i>

1485
01:17:29.778 --> 01:17:32.780
<i>It was called
"The Bulger I Know."</i>

1486
01:17:32.847 --> 01:17:35.293
<i>And the girl on the end
of the line. she said.</i>

1487
01:17:35.317 --> 01:17:37.985
"As if we know any other Bulger

1488
01:17:38.053 --> 01:17:41.055
"You know "Whitey" Bulger.
as if we know any other."

1489
01:17:41.122 --> 01:17:43.724
And the article
wasn't even about...

1490
01:17:43.792 --> 01:17:45.326
It was about Bill Bulger

1491
01:17:45.393 --> 01:17:47.395
and it was written
by Walter Boverini.

1492
01:17:47.462 --> 01:17:49.396
who had served
with him in the Senate.

1493
01:17:49.431 --> 01:17:52.044
And it just hit me
how much his legacy

1494
01:17:52.068 --> 01:17:56.248
<i>and anything that he did
was fading away</i>

1495
01:17:56.272 --> 01:18:00.341
<i>and being overshadowed
by his brother.</i>

1496
01:18:06.214 --> 01:18:09.194
<i>And even. UMass Boston.
where Bulger had been President</i>

1497
01:18:09.218 --> 01:18:12.853
<i>for eight years. didn't even
know that it was about him.</i>

1498
01:18:17.426 --> 01:18:19.360
[melancholic music]

1499
01:18:31.840 --> 01:18:32.973
[Jimmy]<i> As I get older</i>

1500
01:18:33.041 --> 01:18:34.953
<i>I realize. like.
my dad's contemporaries</i>

1501
01:18:34.977 --> 01:18:36.354
<i>are checking out now.</i>

1502
01:18:36.378 --> 01:18:38.579
And guys who remembered him
being a Senator

1503
01:18:38.613 --> 01:18:39.891
they're getting old.

1504
01:18:39.915 --> 01:18:42.850
They're my age. you know.
time moves on.

1505
01:18:48.056 --> 01:18:49.790
<i>The neighborhood
I grew up in is gone.</i>

1506
01:18:49.858 --> 01:18:51.525
<i>It doesn't exist anymore.
There's nothing.</i>

1507
01:18:51.593 --> 01:18:54.172
<i>There's nothing left. there's
yuppies over there now.</i>

1508
01:18:54.196 --> 01:18:57.576
You know. I think some of them
think they live in South Boston

1509
01:18:57.600 --> 01:18:59.066
and it's the place to be.

1510
01:18:59.100 --> 01:19:00.779
but the guys
who made it South Boston.

1511
01:19:00.803 --> 01:19:02.069
<i>the people who lived there.</i>

1512
01:19:02.137 --> 01:19:04.538
<i>they're spread all through
the south shore. you know.</i>

1513
01:19:14.149 --> 01:19:16.917
[brass band playing]

1514
01:19:19.754 --> 01:19:23.057
[indistinct chatter]

1515
01:19:26.494 --> 01:19:29.063
- [William Bulger] It's a big crowd here.
- [man] Yeah. it is.

1516
01:19:32.768 --> 01:19:35.814
[William Bulger]
<i>♪ From the mountains ♪</i>

1517
01:19:35.838 --> 01:19:38.439
<i>♪ To the prairies ♪</i>

1518
01:19:38.506 --> 01:19:43.277
<i>♪ To the oceans
White with foam ♪</i>

1519
01:19:44.846 --> 01:19:49.294
<i>♪ God bless America ♪</i>

1520
01:19:49.318 --> 01:19:54.188
<i>♪ My home sweet home ♪</i>

1521
01:19:54.255 --> 01:19:55.923
[band music fades]

1522
01:19:55.990 --> 01:19:58.025
[man] <i>Sadly. he at least in part</i>

1523
01:19:58.092 --> 01:20:02.429
<i>is going to be remembered
because of his brother.</i>

1524
01:20:02.497 --> 01:20:05.032
<i>I hope at some point
we can at least</i>

1525
01:20:05.099 --> 01:20:06.834
<i>find a way to recognize him</i>

1526
01:20:06.901 --> 01:20:10.538
in the contributions he made
to making this a better place.

1527
01:20:12.907 --> 01:20:16.510
[man]<i> He grew up in modest</i>
<i>circumstances in Southie.</i>

1528
01:20:16.578 --> 01:20:20.114
<i>Southie was a very tightly
knit community.</i>

1529
01:20:20.181 --> 01:20:22.516
<i>so they were a force
under themselves.</i>

1530
01:20:22.584 --> 01:20:24.585
And I think Bill Bulger's
political legacy

1531
01:20:24.652 --> 01:20:29.190
will last for another 100
years in Massachusetts.

1532
01:20:29.257 --> 01:20:32.293
People are gonna remember
him for a long time.

1533
01:20:33.461 --> 01:20:34.829
[drums playing]

1534
01:20:39.334 --> 01:20:41.780
[Bill] <i>He raised nine children.</i>

1535
01:20:41.804 --> 01:20:44.916
<i>He came out of the housing
projects in South Boston.</i>

1536
01:20:44.940 --> 01:20:47.185
got himself
to Boston College High School

1537
01:20:47.209 --> 01:20:48.342
and then to Boston College.

1538
01:20:48.409 --> 01:20:49.877
He went into the military

1539
01:20:49.944 --> 01:20:51.912
so the GI Bill could pay for
his College.

1540
01:20:52.814 --> 01:20:54.192
<i>That should shine through more</i>

1541
01:20:54.216 --> 01:20:56.795
<i>than the shadow of a brother.</i>

1542
01:20:56.819 --> 01:20:58.752
You know. whatever the
transgressions of his brother.

1543
01:20:58.820 --> 01:21:00.487
that should not overshadow
my dad.

1544
01:21:05.226 --> 01:21:06.493
[sentimental music]

1545
01:21:19.641 --> 01:21:21.508
[newsreader]
<i>And we have breaking news now</i>

1546
01:21:21.576 --> 01:21:23.444
<i>about a notorious
Boston mobster.</i>

1547
01:21:23.511 --> 01:21:24.689
[reporter] <i>We're just learning</i>

1548
01:21:24.713 --> 01:21:27.158
<i>that the notorious gangster
James "Whitey" Bulger</i>

1549
01:21:27.182 --> 01:21:29.116
<i>has been killed in prison.</i>

1550
01:21:29.183 --> 01:21:30.618
<i>Officials had just moved him</i>

1551
01:21:30.652 --> 01:21:32.453
<i>to a prison in West Virginia.</i>

1552
01:21:38.393 --> 01:21:41.640
At the height of his power.
"Whitey" Bulger ruled the streets

1553
01:21:41.664 --> 01:21:43.041
with an iron fist.

1554
01:21:43.065 --> 01:21:45.198
But those days are long over.

1555
01:21:45.233 --> 01:21:48.914
Now "Whitey" Bulger is dead
in a prison in West Virginia

1556
01:21:48.938 --> 01:21:52.183
and authorities are trying to
figure out how this happened.

1557
01:21:52.207 --> 01:21:53.807
I'm out in front
of Billy's house.

1558
01:21:53.875 --> 01:21:57.522
By the way. he came home
and we got a fleeting shot of him.

1559
01:21:57.546 --> 01:21:59.457
You know. they just kind of
pulled up and he ran in.

1560
01:21:59.481 --> 01:22:02.416
We did see one man come up.
leave a card in the mailbox

1561
01:22:02.483 --> 01:22:03.862
right there and walk away.

1562
01:22:03.886 --> 01:22:05.419
He didn't want to talk either

1563
01:22:05.486 --> 01:22:07.999
as reaction
continues to come in.

1564
01:22:08.023 --> 01:22:09.290
[reporters chatter]

1565
01:22:11.225 --> 01:22:13.672
[Catherine] <i>I was in my room</i>

1566
01:22:13.696 --> 01:22:17.097
and I could hear people
running down the hallway

1567
01:22:17.165 --> 01:22:18.565
and my friend...

1568
01:22:19.901 --> 01:22:21.146
[breaths deeply]

1569
01:22:21.170 --> 01:22:23.304
[voice breaking]
...stood in the doorway and...

1570
01:22:23.371 --> 01:22:25.506
"Miss Catherine...
Miss Catherine..."

1571
01:22:27.575 --> 01:22:29.421
<i>"It's Jimmy..."</i>

1572
01:22:29.445 --> 01:22:30.822
<i>I thought he had a heart attack</i>

1573
01:22:30.846 --> 01:22:32.646
<i>because he had
mini heart attacks.</i>

1574
01:22:32.714 --> 01:22:35.616
And she said. "He was murdered."

1575
01:22:39.921 --> 01:22:42.323
I screamed.
I literally screamed.

1576
01:22:42.390 --> 01:22:43.568
I couldn't believe it.

1577
01:22:43.592 --> 01:22:46.527
I jumped up
and I ran down the room

1578
01:22:46.594 --> 01:22:48.195
<i>and I think I ran yelling
the whole way</i>

1579
01:22:48.262 --> 01:22:50.597
<i>"'Whitey' Bulger is dead.
He's been killed."</i>

1580
01:22:53.401 --> 01:22:54.668
It was stunning.

1581
01:22:54.736 --> 01:22:57.182
It was really stunning
that he would...

1582
01:22:57.206 --> 01:22:58.706
That it would end that way.

1583
01:23:03.078 --> 01:23:06.613
[Bob Ward] <i>We all knew "Whitey"
Bulger was going to meet his end.</i>

1584
01:23:06.681 --> 01:23:09.817
But still. it's kind of a shock
when it actually happens.

1585
01:23:09.884 --> 01:23:12.820
"Whitey" has been
this larger than life

1586
01:23:12.887 --> 01:23:15.956
figure in South Boston
and in Boston.

1587
01:23:16.024 --> 01:23:18.136
I think all of New England.
for decades.

1588
01:23:18.160 --> 01:23:21.072
<i>And now he's gone.
and it's just kind of hard</i>

1589
01:23:21.096 --> 01:23:23.364
to let that sort of sink
in a little bit.

1590
01:23:26.901 --> 01:23:28.302
Part of me was angry at myself

1591
01:23:28.369 --> 01:23:30.882
because I had visited him
several times in jail

1592
01:23:30.906 --> 01:23:33.240
and it had been a while since
I had visited him

1593
01:23:33.307 --> 01:23:35.909
and I really regretted the fact
that I had not at least gone down

1594
01:23:35.977 --> 01:23:37.311
to visit him.

1595
01:23:37.378 --> 01:23:39.113
you know. one more time.

1596
01:23:39.180 --> 01:23:41.115
When I learned that he died.

1597
01:23:41.182 --> 01:23:43.117
I didn't think of it
as the end of a chapter.

1598
01:23:43.184 --> 01:23:46.920
I thought of it
as who signed the paperwork

1599
01:23:46.988 --> 01:23:48.322
to put him in that prison.

1600
01:23:49.457 --> 01:23:50.657
<i>It was a set up.</i>

1601
01:23:50.725 --> 01:23:54.305
<i>The government executed him
in my opinion.</i>

1602
01:23:54.329 --> 01:23:57.931
[Catherine]<i> He was waiting to
be transferred to a medical facility.</i>

1603
01:23:57.999 --> 01:24:00.845
and instead. somehow
they transferred him

1604
01:24:00.869 --> 01:24:03.537
to the most dangerous...

1605
01:24:03.604 --> 01:24:04.849
[voice breaking]
...prison and put him

1606
01:24:04.873 --> 01:24:07.452
in population immediately.

1607
01:24:07.476 --> 01:24:11.189
No. that's not
one person's mistake.

1608
01:24:11.213 --> 01:24:13.547
That is over-seeing.

1609
01:24:14.949 --> 01:24:17.195
[woman] <i>We are very
aggressively chasing the story</i>

1610
01:24:17.219 --> 01:24:18.619
<i>of "Whitey" Bulger's murder</i>

1611
01:24:18.686 --> 01:24:20.287
because I feel strongly that

1612
01:24:20.354 --> 01:24:23.802
this needs to be
thoroughly investigated.

1613
01:24:23.826 --> 01:24:25.737
There needs to be
accountability.

1614
01:24:25.761 --> 01:24:27.405
And that...

1615
01:24:27.429 --> 01:24:30.297
I'm not just talking about the
people that went into the cell

1616
01:24:30.364 --> 01:24:31.409
and murdered him.

1617
01:24:31.433 --> 01:24:33.611
I'm talking about the people
in the Bureau of Prisons

1618
01:24:33.635 --> 01:24:36.214
who put him in a position
where he could be murdered.

1619
01:24:36.238 --> 01:24:38.172
And that's really
the bigger question.

1620
01:24:48.449 --> 01:24:53.387
[Catherine] <i>He wasn't the person
that was created by the media.</i>

1621
01:24:54.856 --> 01:24:57.791
<i>I don't know how they created
what they did.</i>

1622
01:24:57.859 --> 01:25:01.795
It seems like they needed him
to be a monster.

1623
01:25:03.331 --> 01:25:07.334
<i>I felt like
it was my responsibility</i>

1624
01:25:07.401 --> 01:25:10.904
<i>to try to diminish
this horrible image.</i>

1625
01:25:12.073 --> 01:25:14.274
<i>I thought this is my chance</i>

1626
01:25:15.410 --> 01:25:17.455
to see how my life was

1627
01:25:17.479 --> 01:25:19.746
and it really. truly...

1628
01:25:19.814 --> 01:25:22.082
<i>If I had to do all over again.</i>

1629
01:25:22.150 --> 01:25:23.417
<i>I would go with him.</i>

1630
01:25:28.089 --> 01:25:29.389
[morose music]

1631
01:25:42.303 --> 01:25:45.016
[William Bulger]<i> The subject</i>
<i>that interests so many.</i>

1632
01:25:45.040 --> 01:25:48.686
<i>the life and the activities
of my brother James</i>

1633
01:25:48.710 --> 01:25:50.978
<i>is painful and difficult for me.</i>

1634
01:25:53.047 --> 01:25:57.295
<i>But it is a subject I've lived
with for a long time.</i>

1635
01:25:57.319 --> 01:26:00.387
<i>In truth. my effort with Jim
spanned the decades.</i>

1636
01:26:02.190 --> 01:26:04.191
<i>My attempts to change
my brother's life</i>

1637
01:26:04.258 --> 01:26:06.994
<i>were unsuccessful.</i>

1638
01:26:07.061 --> 01:26:10.531
<i>I wish that I could have
achieved success.</i>

1639
01:26:10.598 --> 01:26:13.066
<i>But I must tell you
that reforming Jim Bulger</i>

1640
01:26:13.134 --> 01:26:18.116
<i>was not my sole
24 hour a day focus.</i>

1641
01:26:18.140 --> 01:26:21.842
<i>I never wrote my brother off
or walled him off.</i>

1642
01:26:23.344 --> 01:26:26.658
<i>but public service
and my own immediate family</i>

1643
01:26:26.682 --> 01:26:29.116
<i>placed very large claims on me.</i>

1644
01:26:31.619 --> 01:26:34.154
<i>And while I worried
about my brother.</i>

1645
01:26:34.222 --> 01:26:36.623
<i>I now recognize
that I didn't fully grasp</i>

1646
01:26:36.691 --> 01:26:38.559
<i>the dimensions of his life.</i>

1647
01:26:47.502 --> 01:26:49.436
[somber music]

1648
01:27:01.716 --> 01:27:03.550
[somber music continues]

1649
01:27:09.056 --> 01:27:11.525
[William praying]
Our Father. Who art in heaven

1650
01:27:11.592 --> 01:27:13.026
hallowed be Thy name.

1651
01:27:13.928 --> 01:27:15.173
Thy kingdom come

1652
01:27:15.197 --> 01:27:16.774
Thy will be done

1653
01:27:16.798 --> 01:27:19.666
on earth as it is in Heaven.

1654
01:27:19.734 --> 01:27:21.579
Give us this day our daily bread

1655
01:27:21.603 --> 01:27:23.136
and forgive us our trespasses

1656
01:27:23.204 --> 01:27:25.772
as we forgive those
who trespass against us.

1657
01:27:26.941 --> 01:27:28.809
And lead us not into temptation

1658
01:27:28.876 --> 01:27:31.545
but deliver us from evil. Amen.

1659
01:27:37.084 --> 01:27:40.887
[somber music]



